XML :
------
         Extensible Markup Language (XML) is a markup language that defines a set of rules for encoding documents in a format which is both human-readable and machine-readable.

Xpath:
-------

1.The XML Path Language, is a query language for selecting nodes from an XML document. In addition, XPath may be used to compute values     (e.g., strings, numbers, or Boolean values) from the content of an XML document. XPath was defined by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C).

2.The XPath language is based on a tree representation of the XML document


